Repost from @conschwartz
•
when Jackson State announced Coach Prime (@deionsanders) as their new head coach and here we are getting ready to kick off the season at the @orangeblossomfc in Miami on Sunday!!! 
 
I am overwhelmed in a number of ways…. 

With humbleness that Jackson, Mississippi and @jacksonstateu welcomed our collective teams into their culture and community to share their story with the COACH PRIME DOC on @barstoolsports. 

I am in awe of these amazing kids, coaches and staff who have overcome a pandemic, water crisis and weather elements that continue to put a strain their daily life but they keep fighting and learning. 

 I am proud of my team at @smacentertainment and also at @wme_sports who came together to find partners that share Coach Prime and our collective vision to shine a light on JSU and ALL HBCU’s so they may level up and get the resources they so deserve. 

And I am lucky to see first hand the  impact the HBCU - @theswac and JSU have on our culture - the @sonicboom_ots is pure MAGIC. 

Thank you to Barstool, especially @ekanardini for believing in this vision and jumping off the bridge when I made the call and she said Let’s GOOOOOOO.  To the amazing production crew - you guys crushed it….. @jensimonssays and Sean (@drhustle) for keeping the ship afloat, @dganunlester and your team for bringing @chevrolet on board. @danabeers, for nailing it! @kshaves and the crack tea, @barstoolbooz, and my Mallone Mallone (@mam_sorini) and our own Ray Donovan! And last but not least special shout out to the OG @snoopdogg who always shows up for the family. 💙

I hope you love these six episodes as much as we loved living them!!! We’re already well into the next six!

Now let’s get our first win this weekend!!!!! 

#IBELIEVE

Julius Jones is an innocent man who has been on death row in Oklahoma for over 20 years. At 19 years old, he was convicted of a murder he did not commit. He was at home with his family during the time of the crime, his family was not given the opportunity to testify in court, and multiple people have come forward saying that someone else, Julius’ co-defendent, confessed to the murder. 

The Oklahoma Attorney General requested that Julius Jones be given an execution date of October 28th despite the state’s troubling history with botched executions, a scheduled commutation hearing, and his maintained innocence.

Join me in demanding #JusticeForJulius and email the Pardon and Parole board to tell them why Julius is innocent and why they should not execute him.
